  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: Since the original 2021 validation campaign, the clinical use case has grown to include paediatric patients and high-flow adult perfusion scenarios (cardiac output up to 7.5 L/min) that were not represented in the validation dataset. No re-calibration or supplemental validation evidence covering the expanded operating envelope has been linked to this package.",
