      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the regulatory acceptance metric. CFD outputs scalar hemolysis index and volume-averaged shear stress, both of which feed directly into the RH calculation. QoI relevance is unchanged across the expanded envelope, though the magnitude and spatial distribution of shear stress differ in paediatric flow regimes."
    },
    {
