      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover the geometry, fluid properties, and operating conditions representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "The 2021 validation campaign used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry with bovine blood under adult CPB conditions, which aligns with the original COU. The assessment team notes that the COU now encompasses paediatric and high-flow adult perfusion regimes introduced in 2023 clinical practice updates. The existing validation evidence predates this expansion and does not cover the new operating range. The team judges the original validation sufficient by extrapolation, but no supplemental validation data have been collected or linked."
